Program: Last Word
Title: 21/05/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00sdgmg
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 23 May 2010
On Last Word this week Major General Khattiya Sawasdipol - otherwise known as "Sae Daeng" or Red Commander. The flamboyant security chief of the red shirted anti-government protesters was shot dead in Bangkok last week. Also Professor Richard Gregory, the eminent psychologist who increased our understanding of human perception Hank Jones - the revered jazz pianist who played with most of the top names of the twentieth century The political columnist Alan Watkins - one of the last greats of Fleet Street And: never knowingly overdressed: the nude pin up of the fifties and sixties, Pamela Green. Show less